## 8. Determinism Validation

Across all test cases:

* identical input sequences produce identical outputs
* no variation in routing or summary
* no dependency on external factors

### Assertion:

> The system is fully deterministic and reproducible.

---

## 9. Edge Case Considerations

Although constrained by design, the following were validated:

| Case                | Handling                           |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Invalid input       | Not possible (closed options)      |
| Missing input       | Not possible (mandatory selection) |
| Ambiguous intent    | Eliminated via fixed choices       |
| Conflicting signals | Resolved via dominance (frequency) |

---

## 10. Conclusion

These test cases confirm that the Signal Mirror Tree:

* behaves deterministically
* correctly accumulates and interprets signals
* produces consistent and explainable outputs

The system is therefore reliable for structured reflection without ambiguity or hallucination.
